{"article_id":"efoSBf5enjQvuzzg","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Former Vice President Joe Biden won what looks to be at least a narrow delegate victory in yesterday 's Super Tuesday contests ,","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"which will award a third of all delegates to the Democratic National Convention in July .","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"While the campaign is far from over ,","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"Sen. Bernie Sanders '","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"( I-Vt. )","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"march to the nomination","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"that looked so likely just a week ago","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"is a long-gone dream for the progressive left .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"As he and his campaign look upon the wreckage of what could have been a casual romp en route to Milwaukee ,","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"they absolutely must correct course","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"and start the difficult process","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"of appealing to mainstream Democrats","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"if they want to have any hope","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"of winning .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"Let 's start with the toplines :","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"It was a bloodbath for Sanders","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"and a bonanza for Biden .","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"States","depth":13},{"id":18,"text":"where Sanders had the inside track just days ago ,","depth":13},{"id":19,"text":"particularly Maine , Minnesota , Texas , and Massachusetts , went for Biden ,","depth":12},{"id":20,"text":"who also won Virginia , North Carolina , Tennessee , Arkansas , Oklahoma , and Alabama .","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"His margin in Virginia alone provided him with enough ballast","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"to survive Sanders ' numbers out West .","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"Sanders got obliterated so badly in Alabama","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"that he likely will get close to zero delegates , just a worst case scenario performance .","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"Overall , Biden won 10 of the 14 states","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"that voted yesterday ,","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"and","depth":13},{"id":28,"text":"while we of course do not know","depth":14},{"id":29,"text":"what the precise delegate totals will be ,","depth":14},{"id":30,"text":"he has opened up a lead on Sanders","depth":13},{"id":31,"text":"that wo n't be easy to overcome .","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"And Sanders was boxed in ,","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"scoring victories only in Vermont , Colorado , Utah , and California .","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"The Golden State win was important ,","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"because it kept him within hailing distance of Biden ,","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"but it was n't nearly as huge","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"as it looked like it might have been recently .","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"If there 's any silver lining for Sanders ,","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"it 's that former New York City Mayor Michael Bloomberg and Massachusetts Sen. Elizabeth Warren reached viability in multiple states ,","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"holding Biden 's margins down a bit","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"and making it dramatically more likely that no one will reach a pledged delegate majority before the convention .","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"But","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"as the dust settles this morning ,","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"Biden has the inside track on at least a strong delegate plurality ,","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"which would make a Sanders nomination virtually unthinkable .","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"The tectonic shift in this race","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"that took place over the last 7 days","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"is unprecedented .","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"On the night of the last Democratic debate","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"before South Carolina voted ,","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"Sanders had a comfortable national lead as well as clear advantages in delegate sinks California and Texas .","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"But Biden delivered a forceful performance in that debate ,","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"blew out Sanders in South Carolina ,","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"and then staged the impressive feat","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"of convincing rivals Pete Buttigieg and Minnesota Sen. Amy Klobuchar to drop out","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"and endorse him in the two days before Super Tuesday .","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"While neither had much of a chance","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"to win ,","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"collectively they controlled about 10 percent of the national electorate .","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"That 's not nothing ,","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"and it looks to have contributed to a massive movement toward Biden among late-breaking voters in the Super Tuesday electorate .","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"What went wrong for Bernie ?","depth":5},{"id":63,"text":"Let 's start with his self-destructive 60 Minutes interview on February 24th .","depth":6},{"id":64,"text":"If there 's one thing","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"that terrifies Democratic elites more than anything itself ,","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"it 's Bernie 's long history","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"of sympathizing with left-wing authoritarians in places like Cuba and Nicaragua .","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"So","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"when he went on national television","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"and praised Fidel Castro 's literacy program from the 1960s ,","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"you could literally hear the faces of party strategists","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"smacking into desks all across the country .","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"There 's an easy way for Sanders","depth":6},{"id":74,"text":"to handle this kind of question :","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"`` I was wrong to say anything positive about Fidel Castro ,","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"who was a brutal tyrant .","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"But American foreign policy in these countries was still catastrophic","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"and we should never side with dictators","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"no matter what side of the political spectrum they happen to fall on . ''","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"Not for this guy .","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"He ca n't do it .","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"He ca n't walk back a mistake .","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"And it 's terrifying .","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"I hope","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"this is obvious by now","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"but there is zero conceivable political benefit","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"to soft-pedaling your criticism of Fidel .","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"Pro-Castro voters in America are like less than 1 percent of the electorate .","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"As Andrew Yang might say :","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"MATH .","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"Someone in a position of authority in the campaign needs to pull Sanders aside","depth":6},{"id":92,"text":"and just give him a script about the 1970s and 1980s","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"and tell him never to deviate from it .","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"Memorize it ,","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"carve it in block letters on his arm ,","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"and read it out robotically","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"whenever anyone asks about Cuba or the Sandinistas .","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"Wash , rinse ,","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"shout , repeat .","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"Sanders also has a real and growing problem","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"building out his coalition .","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"While Biden was rolling up the support of the other Democratic contenders ,","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"what was Sanders doing ?","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"Did anyone reach out to Warren","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"to see","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"if she might drop out","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"and endorse him ?","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"Think of it this way :","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"At one point there were more than 20 Democrats","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"running for president .","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"Most of them have hit the eject button","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"and parachuted back to safety ,","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"and the only two","depth":13},{"id":114,"text":"who endorsed Sanders","depth":13},{"id":115,"text":"were the eccentric lifestyle guru Marianne Williamson and New York City Mayor Bill DeBlasio ,","depth":13},{"id":116,"text":"who was so unpopular","depth":14},{"id":117,"text":"that his candidacy was rejected immediately by the electorate","depth":15},{"id":118,"text":"like he was the wrong blood type for a transfusion .","depth":15},{"id":119,"text":"Was Bernie ever going to be an easy sell to most of these people ?","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"No .","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"But someone like Sen. Cory Booker","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"( D-N.J. ) ,","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"who sports one of the most progressive voting records of anyone in the U.S. Senate ,","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"was probably gettable .","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"So was Sen. Kamala Harris","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"( D-Calif. ) ,","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"whose Senate record is eerily similar to Bernie 's .","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"The fact","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"that they both sat quietly on their hands","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"while the only progressive","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"remaining in the race with a plausible path to victory was surging in the polls","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"should tell you something about the Sanders campaign 's outreach operation .","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"If they do n't have someone on board","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"who can do this kind of thing ,","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"they need to get on it .","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"Yesterday .","depth":9},{"id":137,"text":"Bernie 's troubles","depth":12},{"id":138,"text":"securing the backing of other Democrats","depth":12},{"id":139,"text":"are too broad","depth":12},{"id":140,"text":"to blame on any one particular factor .","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"I noted in September","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"that some personnel calls ,","depth":13},{"id":143,"text":"including the decision","depth":14},{"id":144,"text":"to place strategic communications in the hands of Twitter personality David Sirota ,","depth":14},{"id":145,"text":"seemed almost designed to shrink the Sanders coalition on purpose .","depth":12},{"id":146,"text":"Sure , people like Booker know","depth":14},{"id":147,"text":"who this is .","depth":14},{"id":148,"text":"You can bet","depth":14},{"id":149,"text":"that someone","depth":17},{"id":150,"text":"who works for Jim Clyburn","depth":17},{"id":151,"text":"does .","depth":16},{"id":152,"text":"Journalists","depth":17},{"id":153,"text":"who set campaign narratives","depth":17},{"id":154,"text":"do .","depth":16},{"id":155,"text":"But do normal people care about or even know","depth":13},{"id":156,"text":"who he is ?","depth":13},{"id":157,"text":"No , of course not .","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"It 's a zero upside play with massive downside ,","depth":12},{"id":159,"text":"in the same way","depth":13},{"id":160,"text":"that trotting Bull Durham star and 2016 Jill Stein voter Susan Sarandon out at campaign events is just mind-bogglingly self-destructive .","depth":13},{"id":161,"text":"Everyone in the Sanders orbit was perfectly justified","depth":12},{"id":162,"text":"by pushing back hard on the insane McGovern hysteria","depth":13},{"id":163,"text":"that has gripped party elites since Iowa .","depth":13},{"id":164,"text":"To reiterate :","depth":9},{"id":165,"text":"The electability case for Sanders is almost indistinguishable from the one for Biden .","depth":10},{"id":166,"text":"But Sanders would have been well advised to do something , anything ,","depth":11},{"id":167,"text":"to placate nervous Democrats , particularly older black voters","depth":12},{"id":168,"text":"who are n't inclined to gamble another four years of Trump on a Sanders nomination .","depth":12},{"id":169,"text":"There 's still time ,","depth":10},{"id":170,"text":"but it 's running out .","depth":10},{"id":171,"text":"This race is far from over .","depth":10},{"id":172,"text":"With Warren almost certainly on the way out ,","depth":13},{"id":173,"text":"and with Bloomberg reassessing his chances ,","depth":13},{"id":174,"text":"it could be a two-person scrum as early as the end of this week .","depth":12},{"id":175,"text":"Biden probably has no better than a high double-digit delegate lead on Sanders with 60 percent of delegates","depth":13},{"id":176,"text":"to come ,","depth":13},{"id":177,"text":"and a contested convention is a significant possibility .","depth":12},{"id":178,"text":"In short :","depth":9},{"id":179,"text":"Almost anything is still possible .","depth":9},{"id":180,"text":"If Sanders and his team are serious about winning this nomination ,","depth":9},{"id":181,"text":"they need to scramble for support","depth":10},{"id":182,"text":"- from Warren , from any Democrat with clout , and from voters","depth":11},{"id":183,"text":"who like the Sanders platform","depth":12},{"id":184,"text":"but have reservations about his chances in the general election .","depth":12},{"id":185,"text":"If they are unable or unwilling to do that ,","depth":9},{"id":186,"text":"they should resign themselves to gritting through Biden 's acceptance speech in Milwaukee .","depth":9},{"id":187,"text":"For Joe Biden , his reputation as a Democratic primary loser is gone ,","depth":11},{"id":188,"text":"having staged maybe the greatest last minute comeback in primary history .","depth":11},{"id":189,"text":"A prize","depth":12},{"id":190,"text":"that he has sought now four times since 1984","depth":12},{"id":191,"text":"is finally within his reach ,","depth":11},{"id":192,"text":"and his gambit","depth":11},{"id":193,"text":"to unify Democrats around his candidacy","depth":11},{"id":194,"text":"looks prescient .","depth":10},{"id":195,"text":"But he too needs to reach out , if not to Sanders stalwarts ,","depth":10},{"id":196,"text":"then to Warren supporters","depth":11},{"id":197,"text":"who might otherwise gravitate to Sanders .","depth":11},{"id":198,"text":"If he does n't expand his coalition","depth":11},{"id":199,"text":"to include more ramparts of the left ,","depth":11},{"id":200,"text":"he might also find himself with an impossible task at the convention , or worse , in charge of a party so disunited","depth":11},{"id":201,"text":"that it ca n't win in the fall .","depth":11},{"id":202,"text":"Want more essential commentary and analysis like this delivered straight to your inbox ?","depth":2},{"id":203,"text":"Sign up for The Week 's `` Today 's best articles '' newsletter here .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":407,"left":405,"right":406,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":405,"left":265,"right":404,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":265,"left":217,"right":264,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":217,"left":205,"right":216,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":205,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":216,"left":210,"right":215,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":210,"left":2,"right":209,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":209,"left":208,"right":7,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":208,"left":206,"right":207,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":206,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":207,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":215,"left":213,"right":214,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":213,"left":8,"right":212,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":212,"left":9,"right":211,"relat